# Testing

## Frameworks

| Layer | Framework | Location |
|-------|-----------|----------|
| Backend | **pytest** | `backend/tests/` |
| Frontend | **Playwright** | `frontend/e2e/` |

Do not introduce alternate test runners (e.g. Jest/Vitest for UI, unittest for API) without an explicit project decision.

## Make targets

- `make test_server` — backend unit tests (`uv run pytest`)
- `make test_frontend` — Playwright e2e tests (`npm run test` in `frontend/`)
- `make ci` — both; used by GitHub Actions on PRs and pushes to `main`

## Writing tests

**Backend:** Use pytest with `httpx`/`TestClient` for API tests. Prefer `tmp_path` fixtures for config and SQLite; avoid touching the developer’s `.data/` directory.

**Frontend:** Use `@playwright/test` against the built app via Vite preview (see `frontend/playwright.config.ts`). Assert user-visible behaviour (roles, text), not implementation details.

## CI

`.github/workflows/ci.yml` runs `make ci` on pull requests targeting `main` and on pushes to `main`.

## Known noise

`@tailwindcss/node` (Tailwind v4 Vite plugin) triggers Node `DEP0205` (`module.register` deprecation) during `vite build`. Frontend npm scripts set `NODE_OPTIONS=--disable-warning=DEP0205` until upstream fixes it.
